      int elevation
      Elevation of the Feedback Bar from the Frame background.
      boolean enablePulsatingText
      Control whether to enable the pulsating-text animation within the Feedback Bar.
      Default is true (enabled).
      float relativeWidth
      Control the percent of the available Frame width to use for the Feedback Bar's width.
      Relative width percent is represented in decimal notation, ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f.
      If the value configured is equal to or greater than 1.0f, the Feedback Bar will be drawn to at max width within the Frame.
      If the value configured results in a width that is less than the minimum width, which is 2x the Feedback Bar's height, then the Feedback Bar's width will be set at the minimum.
      Default is dynamically configured per device at runtime.
      int textColor
      Color of the text displayed within the Feedback Bar.

        public int textSize
        Size of the text displayed within the Feedback Bar.
        This value is calculated in scaled pixels (i.e. TypedValue.COMPLEX_UNIT_SP).
        Default is dynamically configured per device at runtime.

      • enablePulsatingText

        public boolean enablePulsatingText
        Control whether to enable the pulsating-text animation within the Feedback Bar.
        Default is true (enabled).

      • elevation

        public int elevation
        Elevation of the Feedback Bar from the Frame background. Only available for API >= 21.
        This value is calculated in density/device-independent pixels (i.e. TypedValue.COMPLEX_UNIT_DIP).
        Default is dynamically configured per device at runtime.

      • relativeWidth

        public float relativeWidth
        Control the percent of the available Frame width to use for the Feedback Bar's width.
        Relative width percent is represented in decimal notation, ranging from 0.0f to 1.0f.
        If the value configured is equal to or greater than 1.0f, the Feedback Bar will be drawn to at max width within the Frame.
        If the value configured results in a width that is less than the minimum width, which is 2x the Feedback Bar's height, then the Feedback Bar's width will be set at the minimum.
        Default is dynamically configured per device at runtime.
